# Custom Multi-Asset Index Construction

## Overview
This project builds a custom equity index using factor-based portfolio construction. The index selects and weights securities based on momentum and market capitalization, with systematic monthly rebalancing.

## Key Features
- Analyzed 30+ equities using 2+ years of historical data
- Implemented momentum-based signal generation
- Designed market-cap weighted portfolio construction
- Monthly rebalancing across 24+ periods
- Performance benchmarking vs S&P 500

## Methodology

### 1. Data Processing
- Collected historical price data
- Cleaned and aligned time series
- Computed returns and rolling metrics

### 2. Signal Generation
- Momentum factor based on past returns
- Ranked securities based on signal strength

### 3. Portfolio Construction
- Selected top 10 securities per rebalance period
- Weighted portfolio using market capitalization

### 4. Rebalancing Strategy
- Monthly portfolio updates
- Adjusted weights dynamically based on signals

### 5. Performance Evaluation
- Total returns
- Sharpe ratio
- Maximum drawdown

## Results
- Built a systematic index with dynamic allocation
- Demonstrated factor-driven portfolio behavior
- Compared performance against S&P 500 benchmark

## Tech Stack
- Python (Pandas, NumPy)
- Matplotlib / Seaborn
- Time Series Analysis

## Future Improvements
- Add risk parity weighting
- Incorporate multi-factor signals (value, volatility)
- Backtest with transaction costs
